    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for the house i'm buying in toronto. i've never heard of that before... what exactly is escrow and why do i need it for the closing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow, in the context of a real estate purchase, is essentially a neutral third party holding funds and documents until all the terms of the sale are met. Think of it like a temporary holding space for your money and the necessary paperwork. It's crucial because it protects both you, the buyer, and the seller, ensuring that the money doesn't go to the seller until you have legally received the house, and the house doesn't transfer until the funds are verified. It's a standard procedure in many real estate transactions, including in Toronto.",
