    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The money is typically held by a specialized, neutral third party, which is usually a real estate lawyer or a licensed title company, not your realtor directly. These professionals are legally obligated to manage the funds according to strict regulations, ensuring they are secure and accounted for. They act as the gatekeepers, making sure the transaction proceeds smoothly and fairly for both parties. You can trust these regulated entities to keep your funds safe throughout the closing process.",
